  • Classes in org.nmdp.ngs.hml.jaxb used by org.nmdp.ngs.hml.jaxb 
    Class and Description
    Allele
    An allele element specifies a single allele: it should be given in LOCUS*NAME format and names must be at allele-level resolution (NOTE: This element and its children were deprecated in HML 1.0).
    AlleleAssignment
    Specifies the genotyping call at the most specific level possible.
    AlleleList
    An allele-list element is a representation of the list of allele possibilities for a genotype (NOTE: This element and its children were deprecated in HML 1.0).
    Amplification
    Identifies the amplification primer used for SBT-Sanger, and the resulting sequence from using it.
    ConsensusSequence
    Describes a sequence that is the result of an alignment or assembly of shorter sequence reads generated by an NGS platform.
    ConsensusSequenceBlock
    Java class for anonymous complex type.
    DiploidCombination
    A diploid-combination element is one possibility value in a genotype- list (NOTE: This element and its children were deprecated in HML 1.0).
    GenotypeList
    A genotype-list represents a full unambiguous list of possibilities for the typing of a sample (NOTE: This element and its children were deprecated in HML 1.0).
    Glstring
    Specifies a resource in Genotype List String (GL String) format for the interpretation of a typing result, or a URI identifying a resource in GL String format.
    Gssp
    Describes the Group Specific Sequencing Primer used.
    Haploid
    Specifies one-half of a full typing at a particular locus.
    Hml
    Java class for anonymous complex type.
    Hmlid
    Specifies a unique identifier for this HML document.
    LocusBlock
    A locus-block element allows allele-list elements to be grouped together to mean one allele-list is a possibility if and only if all others are (NOTE: This element and its children were deprecated in HML 1.0).
    Present
    Java class for present.
    Property
    Allows the optional inclusion of key-value pairs (not defined explicitly by the schema) without the need to extend or change the schema.
    RawReads
    Reports the raw sequence reads generated by an NGS platform.
    ReferenceDatabase
    Java class for anonymous complex type.
    ReferenceDatabase.ReferenceSequence
    Java class for anonymous complex type.
    ReportingCenter
    Java class for anonymous complex type.
    Sample
    Encloses the genotyping data pertaining to a particular sample.
    SbtNgs
    Describes an NGS (next-generation sequencing) event that was performed.
    SbtSanger
    Describes an SBT (sequence-based typing) that was performed using a Sanger technique.
    Sequence
    The DNA alphabet consists of primary nucleotides (A, C, G, T).
    SequenceQuality
    Java class for anonymous complex type.
    Sso
    Specifies an SSO (sequence-specific oligonucleotide) test that was done for this sample.
    Ssp
    Specifies an SSP (sequence-specific primer) test that was performed for this sample.
    SubAmplification
    Identifies sub-amplification primers.
    Typing
    Encapsulates the primary data from a genotyping method with an optional genotyping result (allele-assignment) determined from the primary data and/or optional consensus sequences.
    TypingMethod
    Java class for anonymous complex type.
    TypingTestName
    Specifies a single test name contained in a referenced "typing-test- names" list.
    TypingTestNames
    Specifies a list of test names internally referenced by an "sso" element or an "ssp" element.
    Variant
    Java class for anonymous complex type.
    VariantEffect
    Java class for anonymous complex type.
